Vice President Mike Pence and President Moon Jae-in of South Korea met on the sidelines of the East Asia Summit. They reaffirmed the importance of the U.S.-South Korea alliance for peace and security in the region. They discussed ongoing efforts to achieve the denuclearization of North Korea and establish a permanent peace on the Korean Peninsula. Pence and Moon emphasized the need for close coordination on North Korea-related matters, including sanctions and inter-Korean cooperation. They committed to maintaining close communication between their countries.